Ready-to-eat food businesses live on thin margins for error. Temperature, handling, sanitation, and shelf life all conspire to punish laziness.

## Why this brand stands out

Made Fresh Salads appears often enough in the FDA record to justify a dedicated report. The company operates in a category where contamination scares move quickly from plant issue to consumer issue, and that raises the stakes on every process slip.

## The scorecard view

Shelf Check's Accountability Score does not care whether a brand sounds wholesome. It cares whether the underlying pattern suggests control or drift. In this case, the pattern leans toward drift.

## Bottom line

Consumers should not panic, but they should pay attention. If a refrigerated convenience brand starts showing up repeatedly in recall databases, that's not random static. That's the product category telling you how fragile the operation really is.
